# INRestaurantResolutionResult

**Class**

A resolution result for the restaurant selected by a user.

## Declaration

```swift
class INRestaurantResolutionResult
```

## Overview

An [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INRestaurantResolutionResult] object is what you return when resolving parameters containing an [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INRestaurant] object. Use the creation method that best reflects your ability to successfully resolve the parameter. For additional resolution options, see [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INIntentResolutionResult].

## Creating a Resolution Result Object

- **success(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves the successful matching of the specified parameter.
- **confirmationRequired(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires that the user must confirm the value before proceeding.
- **disambiguation(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires the user to select from among the specified objects.

## Resolution Results

- **INRestaurantGuestResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the identity of a user involved in booking a reservation at a restaurant.

- INIntentResolutionResult
